Ticket: Recover Deleted Files After Recycle Bin Was Emptied
Issue Description

User accidentally deleted a folder containing client proposals and contracts, then emptied the Recycle Bin approximately two hours later. The user requested assistance recovering the deleted files.

Symptoms
Folder no longer visible in File Explorer.
Windows Recycle Bin is empty.
User reports accidental deletion of important business documents.
Troubleshooting Performed
Connected to the user's computer using Tools → Remote Support.
Verified that the deleted folder was no longer present in File Explorer.
Opened Cloud Drive and initiated a Sync to ensure the latest cloud state was available.
Navigated to Cloud Drive → Version History → Recently Deleted Files.
Located the deleted folder and restored it.
Verified that all files were successfully recovered.
Confirmed with the user that the restored files were accessible.
Resolution

Recovered the deleted folder from the cloud service's Recently Deleted Files and verified that all files were successfully restored.

Status: Resolved

Root Cause

The folder was accidentally deleted and the Windows Recycle Bin was emptied. The files remained recoverable because the cloud storage platform retained deleted items within its recovery retention period.

Preventive Recommendations
Enable automatic cloud synchronization for important folders.
Verify the contents of the Recycle Bin before permanently emptying it.
Maintain regular backups of critical business documents.
Educate users on the available file recovery options provided by the organization's cloud storage platform.
Technical Summary

Even after the local Windows Recycle Bin is emptied, cloud storage platforms may retain deleted files for a defined retention period. Synchronize the client with the cloud service, access the deleted items or version history, restore the required files, and verify successful recovery with the user.

